  "text": "If one considers the fact that like other clitellates, T. tubifex is a 'direct developer' that develops into a juvenile without any larval form, the stomodeal expression of Brachyury as seen in Tubifex could be regarded as an exceptional case, since the stomodeal Brachyury expression is undetectable in tunicates, acraniates, vertebrates, insects and nematodes, all of which develop directly or indirectly by means of larvae other than ciliary larvae [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Only one exception is the direct developing chaetognath Paraspadella gotoi that exhibits",
